Police in Nakuru have launched a manhunt for a corporal caroline Kangogo, suspected to have had a hand in the murder of yet another officer, constable John Ogweno, both of whom were stationed at the Nakuru central police station. Nakuru county deputy police commander joseph Tanui says Kangogo, who is alleged to have been in a romantic relationship with Ogweno despite her being married, vanished with constable Ogweno's pistol that had 15 rounds of ammunition. Meanwhile in Nairobi, investigating officers have asked for 14 days to continue with their probe in which an officer attached to the directorate of criminal investigations DCI, is suspected it has pushed a lady off the fourth floor of a building.